OL,3,CWoman fears being kept alive to suffer
OL,4,Cinstead of being allowed to die
OL,6,FFor Anne, she said knowing she has the
OL,7,Fchoice to die would provide "peace of
OL,8,Fmind".
OL,10,F"It would be so reassuring," she told
OL,11,FITV News. "Because, by golly, this
OL,12,Fcondition I have, is so generous - it
OL,13,Fjust keeps giving. And it is getting
OL,14,Fworse."
OL,16,FIn Anne's case, there is a further
OL,17,Fproblem. The new bill would only give
OL,18,Fthe right to die to terminally ill
OL,19,Fpeople but Anne wants to die before
OL,20,Fthat stage.
