OL,3,CWoman fears being kept alive to suffer
OL,4,Cinstead of being allowed to die
OL,6,F"Where is the justice in that?"
OL,8,FAnne's only option at the moment is
OL,9,Fpalliative care, which aims to manage
OL,10,Fthe symptoms of those with serious
OL,11,Fconditions.
OL,13,FBut she said she fears being "kept
OL,14,Falive" while suffering, similarly to
OL,15,Fwhat her mother experienced after
OL,16,Fhaving a severe stroke.
OL,18,F"The fantastic care in the hospice and
OL,19,Fthe nursing home - and it really was
OL,20,Foutstanding - succeeded in extending
OL,21,Fher life by three years."
